TY  - JOUR
AB  - Certain objections to 100 per cent reserves are commonly overlooked. In case of bank credit, the real lenders are the depositors including, notably, the recipients of checks. It is these whose convenience waiting is combined and co&#xf6;rdinated by the banks and made available to borrowers who pay for free banking service to depositors. The 100 per cent reserve scheme would make this free service impossible unless subsidized and might conceivably bring disappearance of deposit banking. Subsidization objected to; perpetual government debt as means to idea of 100 per cent objected to. Why precisely 100 per cent? A sacred number? Possible resulting growth of new type of financial institution through which we could still get deflation. Why henceforth deprive depositors of possibility of free banking service?
